title: strange debuginfo generated for empty lines

labels.name: A-LLVM
labels.description: Area: Code generation parts specific to LLVM. Both correctness bugs and optimization-related issues.

labels.name: A-debuginfo
labels.description: Area: Debugging information in compiled programs (DWARF, PDB, etc.)

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-stable
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from one stable version to another.

body:
original issue here: https://github.com/mattgodbolt/compiler-explorer/issues/832 It seems that strange debuginfo generated for empty lines that don't actually contain any code. I tried to get some asm with debugginfo for this code (line 1 intentionally left blank) ````rust pub fn test() { let mut v: Vec = Vec::new(); v.push(1); v.push(2); v.push(3); println!("my vector is: {:?}", v); } fn main() { test(); } ```` ````RUSTFLAGS="--emit asm -C codegen-units=1" cargo build ```` asm:
expand
